articles.author: BILL BARROW
articles.description: PLAINS, Ga. (AP) — The Washington chattering class, often unsure what to make of outsiders, dubbed Rosalynn Carter the “Steel Magnolia” when she arrived as first lady.A devout Baptist and mother of four, she was diminutive and outwardly shy, with a soft smile and softer Southern accent.
articles.title: Rosalynn Carter: Advocate for Jimmy Carter and many others, always leveraging her love of politics

articles.description: ATLANTA (AP) — Reactions to the death of Rosalynn Carter, former first lady and global humanitarian:___
articles.title: Reactions to the death of Rosalynn Carter, former first lady and global humanitarian

articles.author: DANIEL POLITI and DAVID BILLER
articles.description: BUENOS AIRES, Argentina (AP) — Populist Javier Milei resoundingly won Argentina's presidential election Sunday, swinging the country to the right following a fiercely polarized campaign in which he promised a dramatic shake-up to the state to deal with soaring inflation and rising poverty.
articles.title: Fiery right-wing populist Javier Milei wins Argentina's presidency and promises 'drastic' changes

articles.author: NAJIB JOBAIN and SAMY MAGDY
articles.description: KHAN YOUNIS, Gaza Strip (AP) — Health officials said 31 premature babies in “extremely critical condition” were transferred safely Sunday from Gaza 's main hospital and will go to Egypt, while over 250 patients with severely infected wounds and other urgent conditions remained stranded days after Israeli forces entered the compound to look for Hamas operations.
articles.title: 31 premature babies are evacuated from Gaza's largest hospital, but scores of trauma patients remain

articles.author: JILL COLVIN, PAUL J. WEBER and MICHELLE L. PRICE
articles.description: EDINBURG, Texas (AP) — Donald Trump picked up the Texas governor’s endorsement Sunday during a visit to a U.S.-Mexico border town and promised that his hard-line immigration policies in a second presidential term would make Greg Abbott’s “job much easier.”
articles.title: Trump picks up the endorsement of Texas Gov. Greg Abbott during a visit to a US-Mexico border town

articles.author: WILL WEISSERT
articles.description: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) — President Joe Biden visited naval installations in Virginia on Sunday to kick off the Thanksgiving holiday week, introducing an early screening of the upcoming movie “Wonka” and sharing a “friendsgiving” meal with service members and their relatives.
articles.title: The Bidens start Thanksgiving early by serving dinner and showing 'Wonka' to service members

articles.author: JULIE CARR SMYTH and CHRISTINE FERNANDO
articles.description: COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) — The statewide battles over abortion rights since the U.S. Supreme Court overturned a constitutional right to abortion have exposed another fault line: the commitment to democracy.
articles.title: Voters back abortion rights, but some foes won’t relent. Is the commitment to democracy in question?

articles.author: LUCAS DUMPHREYS and DIANE JEANTET
articles.description: POCONE, BRAZIL (AP) — Firefighters in Brazil's Pantanal wetlands earlier this month celebrated the end of the fire season on Facebook, saying in a Nov. 7 post that “it is a relief for everyone who lives in the region.”
articles.title: Fires in Brazil threaten jaguars, houses and plants in the world's largest tropical wetlands

articles.author: MICHAEL HILL
articles.description: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) — For a year, a special New York law has cleared the way for a wave of headline-grabbing lawsuits against famous men accused of sexual misconduct, including former President Donald Trump, hip hop mogul Sean “Diddy” Combs and the comedian and actor Russell Brand.
articles.title: The Adult Survivors Act launched over 2,500 sex abuse suits. Now, it’s expiring

articles.author: RALPH D. RUSSO
articles.description: Ohio State passed Michigan and moved up to No. 2 in The Associated Press college football poll Sunday, a week before the Big Ten rivals play another top-five matchup, and No.
articles.title: AP Top 25: Ohio State jumps Michigan, moves to No. 2. Washington, FSU flip-flop at Nos. 4-5
